 IP Moves  
 Google Hires EFF Copyright Specialist Fred von Lohmann  
 Google Inc., operator of the world’s most-used search
engine, hired Fred von Lohmann as senior copyright counsel to
coordinate the company’s global copyright efforts.  
 Von Lohmann  is leaving San Francisco-based  Electronic
Frontier Foundation , a digital-rights advocacy group, where he
was a senior staff attorney.  
 At EFF, von Lohmann has represented programmers, technology
innovators, and individuals in a variety of copyright and
trademark litigation. The best-known was the dispute over the
Grokster file-sharing technology that went to the U.S. Supreme
Court.  
 Before he joined EFF, von Lohmann was a visiting researcher
at the  Berkeley Center for Law and Technology  at the University
of California, Berkeley, School of Law. Before that, he was an
associate at San Francisco-based  Morrison & Foerster LLP .  
 Von Lohmann has an undergraduate degree and a law degree
from Stanford University.  
